cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.CL 

The paper proposes a new neural network activation function and evaluates its performance against other commonly used activation functions. This falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the connection between the proposed activation function and a stochastic regularizer, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The empirical evaluation includes tasks related to computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
